KALGOORLIE (miningweekly.com) â€“ Iron-ore miner Roy Hill on Tuesday revealed ambitions to increase its production at its namesake operation, in the Pilbara, from 55-million tonnes a year to 60-million tonnes a year. Speaking at Diggers & Dealers, in Kalgoorlie, Roy Hill CEO Barry Fitzgerald noted that the company had already received approvals for the expansion, and was hoping to achieve the sustained shipping rate of 60-million tonnes a year by the end of the 2020 financial year. Roy Hill first started iron-ore production in 2016.